25 be required to meet the income verification requirements of § 42-128-8.1. The monitoring agent
26 shall provide a listing of the eligible units to Rhode Island Housing, who shall provide a report as
27 to the qualifying mobile or manufactured homes under this subsection (9) to the governor, speaker
28 of the house of representatives, senate president, and secretary of housing on an annual basis,
29 beginning on or before December 31, 2025.
30 (iii) Low- or moderate-income housing also includes rental property located within a
31 municipality that is secured with a federal government rental assistance voucher.
32 (iv) For the period beginning on or after July 1, 2024, any housing unit that qualifies as
33 low- or moderate-income housing under this subsection (9) and under § 42-128-8.1 and any rental
34 property secured with a federal government rental assistance voucher that does not otherwise meet
